      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 170, Number 37 (Thursday, February 29, 2024)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Ms. CARAVEO:H.R. 7487.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Constitutional Authority--Necessary and Proper Clause (Art.I, Sec. 8, Clause 18)THE U.S. CONSTITUTIONARTICLE I, SECTION 8: POWERS OF CONGRESSCLAUSE 18The single subject of this legislation is:To statutorily establish Operation Stonegarden, throughwhich eligible law enforcement agencies shall be awardedgrants for border security enhancement. Additonally this billprovide enhanced resources for local law enforcement agenciesacross the country.[Page H773]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
